pg| ***** 30 ***** |


cp||sk||NT|^B@2
Even if East has another club, his partner has one also, so that the loss of a club trick cannot defeat your contract. As it happens, East has no more clubs, and must lead a spade, a heart, or a diamond. Whichever of these suits East chooses, you can claim the balance of the tricks.|
pg| ***** 31 ***** |


NT|^B@2
The hold-up is one of the simplest bits of strategy in the play of any hand, but it is also one of the most important plays in any good player's repertoire. |
PG| ***** 32 ***** |


AT|

There is a strangely prevailing opinion among average players that the use of the hold-up is confined to Aces. Actually the play can be used with cards as low as the Jack.|
pg| ***** 33 ***** |


NT|^B@2
