{ WHEN THE SITUATION DOES NOT CALL FOR THE HOLD-UP }
^-|FP||cp||at|^B@2^Y@3
T|FP||AT|he ^*Ihold-up^*N is not the proper play when you hold more than 1 potential trick in that suit. In the two examples just given, the hold-up was effective because you held only one possible stopper in the suit attacked by the Opponents. Sometimes the suit opened against you is one in which you hold the Ace accompanied by certain lower cards which can be developed if you do not employ the hold-up, but which will be valueless if you hold up the Ace. This fact is due to the promotional value of honors.|
